er' | 'challenge_completed' | 'bonus_completed' |\n2100\t    'crate_points'`) is the single source of truth for valid values.\n2101\t  - `listCrateDrops({ sql, limit, filters })` — per-user crate ledger from\n2102\t    `crate_drops` joined with `player_profiles` for both username and\n2103\t    wallet. `crate_drops` has no wallet column of its own; the join uses\n2104\t    `player_profiles.wallet` and the type marks the result `wallet:\n2105\t    string | null` so an orphaned crate-drop row (no FK constraint, but in\n2106\t    practice every drop has a profile) renders honestly. Filters:\n2107\t    `userId`, `crateType`, `status`, `triggerType`, and the\n2108\t    `[createdFrom, createdTo)` window. Default 100, max 500. Ordered by\n2109\t    `created_at desc, id desc`.\n2110\t- New view-model types in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n2111\t  - `PeekPlayerPointsRow` / `PeekPlayerPointsFilters` — cross-user\n2112\t    `player_points` row + filter contract (`userId`, `wallet`).\n2113\t  - `PeekPointGrantLedgerRow` / `PeekPointGrantFilters` — extends the\n2114\t    existing per-user `PeekPointGrantRow` (kept for the user-detail page)\n2115\t    with `userId` / `username` / `wallet` so the cross-user grants page can\n2116\t    render rows with identity context. Filters cover `userId`, `sourceType`,\n2117\t    `sourceId`, and date range.\n2118\t  - `PeekCrateDropLedgerRow` / `PeekCrateDropFilters` — extends the existing\n2119\t    per-user `PeekCrateDropRow` with the same identity columns; `wallet` is\n2120\t    nullable because `crate_drops` has no wallet column. Filters cover\n2121\t    `userId`, `crateType`, `status`, `triggerType`, and date range.\n2122\t- `clampLimit` mirrors the existing rewards/growth pattern (non-finite →\n2123\t  fallback, ≤0 → 1, ≥max → max). `trimOrNull` is the standard filter input\n2124\t  normalizer used in the growth claims query so empty strings don't leak\n2125\t  past as bogus `=` filters.\n2126\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm typecheck` ✅